# Testing and verification

## Backend ladder

| Step | Command | When |
|---|---|---|
| Build | `go build ./...` | Always |
| Focused | `go test -race -count=1 ./<package>/...` (or `/test-affected`) | During iteration |
| Race suite (**floor**) | `go test -race -timeout 10m ./...` (or `/race`) | Runtime/backend changes |
| E2E | `go test -tags e2e ./e2e/...` | api → orchestrator → providers/sandbox/mcp chain |

Race suite is the floor for any change touching `internal/gateway`, `internal/router`, `internal/providers`, `internal/orchestrator`, `internal/sandbox`, or retention/state wiring. Not a nice-to-have.

## UI ladder

| Step | Command | When |
|---|---|---|
| Type check | `cd ui && bun run typecheck` | First sanity check after edits |
| Tests | `cd ui && bun run test` | Before committing |

**Never `bun test`** — it skips testing-library DOM setup and panics with `document[isPrepared]`. Always `bun run test`.

## Test layer choice (quick guide)

- **Unit** — data transformation, wire-shape passthrough, error classification, retry/failover decisions, streaming wire shape, usage accumulation, agent_loop tool dispatch, MCP tool registration, UI data-to-prop transformation, conditional rendering of critical states.
- **Integration** — multi-package wiring within the runtime, such as governor + usage store, router + retention, or orchestrator + taskstate.
- **E2E** — api → orchestrator → providers/sandbox/mcp chain end-to-end; subprocess lifecycle; startup/config semantics; new SSE event sequences operators rely on; public HTTP contract changes.

